description: The site of a very substantial Romano-British building. The excavators favoured a religious function for the site in lack of any domestic material, but there seems to be little to assert this.
bibliography: Bailey, C. J. “The Romano-British Site at Walls, Puncknowle, Dorset.” Proceedings of the Dorset Natural History and Archaeological Society 107 (1985): 55–86.
Martyn, Blick, Brindle, and et al. “Walls, Puncknowle (Dorset).” The Rural Settlement of Roman Britain: an online resource, 2015. https://doi.org/10.5284/1030449.
